Subject: [PATCH] arm: LLVMLinux: Calculate current_thread_info from fp
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Clang requires an extra asm annotation in order to be able to use a named
register. This change supports being able to compile the kernel with both gcc
and Clang.

Signed-off-by: Behan Webster <behanw@converseincode.com>
Reviewed-by: Mark Charlebois <charlebm@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Jan-Simon MÃ¶ller <dl9pf@gmx.de>
---
 arch/arm/include/asm/thread_info.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/include/asm/thread_info.h b/arch/arm/include/asm/thread_info.h
index 71a06b2..9e9306b 100644
--- a/arch/arm/include/asm/thread_info.h
+++ b/arch/arm/include/asm/thread_info.h
@@ -107,6 +107,7 @@ static inline struct thread_info *current_thread_info(void) __attribute_const__;
 static inline struct thread_info *current_thread_info(void)
 {
 	register unsigned long sp asm ("sp");
+	asm("" : "=r"(sp));
 	return (struct thread_info *)(sp & ~(THREAD_SIZE - 1));
 }
 
